## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/fixedstreamarray">FixedStreamArray</a> is similar to <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/varstreamarray">VarStreamArray</a>, except with each record having a fixed-length.

As with <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/varstreamarray">VarStreamArray</a>, there is no upfront cost associated with building or copying a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/fixedstreamarray">FixedStreamArray</a>, as the memory for each element is not read from the backing stream until that element is iterated.

Definition at line 259 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/binarystreamarray-h">BinaryStreamArray.h</a>.
